CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,FIt maintains the overall spending
OL,7,Fplans of the previous Labour Welsh
OL,8,FGovernment but adds #145m towards
OL,9,Fcutting waiting lists in hospitals
OL,10,Falong with #55m towards childcare
OL,11,Ffunding and spending on school
OL,12,Fmaintenance and other capital projects.
OL,14,FPlaid Cymru was the largest party
OL,15,Fafter May's Senedd election so forms
OL,16,Fthe Welsh Government, but it doesn't
OL,17,Fhave a majority so needs the support
OL,18,Fof another party in order to win votes.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,432,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,FThe main opposition party, Reform UK
OL,7,FWales, ruled out backing it saying
OL,8,Fthat it failed to put Wales first, and
OL,9,F"takes money from children with
OL,10,Fadditional learning needs while
OL,11,Fcontinuing to send taxpayers' money
OL,12,Fabroad." Welsh Conservatives also said
OL,13,Fthey wouldn't back it.
OL,15,FToday both have stated to ITV Cymru
OL,16,FWales that no formal talks or
OL,17,Fapproaches have been made and they
OL,18,Freiterated their decision to vote
OL,19,Fagainst the supplementary budget.
OL,26,@qD@AOUtD@HO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,432,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,FTalks have been taking place with
OL,7,FWelsh Labour, but they haven't gone
OL,8,Fsmoothly. Labour has made spending on
OL,9,FAdditional Learning Needs (ALN) in
OL,10,Fschool the focus of negotiations.
OL,12,FAs a result of spending in England
OL,13,Frelated to ALN, the Welsh Government
OL,14,Freceived a #327m boost to its budget
OL,15,Ffor this financial year.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
