PN,43109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,FIn response, a Plaid Cymru source said
OL,7,Fthat, "By voting against the
OL,8,FSupplementary Budget, Labour will vote
OL,9,Fagainst #145m to cut NHS waiting
OL,10,Flists, #120m for children with
OL,11,Fadditional learning needs, #55m to
OL,12,Fexpand funded childcare, and #15m for
OL,13,Ffree school meals for secondary pupils
OL,14,Fmost in need. In doing so, Labour has
OL,15,Fabandoned its progressive values.
OL,26,@oD@GOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,432,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,F"Despite inheriting #333m of in-year
OL,7,Fpressures in the NHS, the Welsh
OL,8,FGovernment worked quickly to put a
OL,9,F#120m proposal on the table to build a
OL,10,Fmore sustainable ALN system. Labour
OL,11,Fhave walked away from that offer - a
OL,12,Fmove that will rightly be questioned
OL,13,Fby parents and teachers.
OL,15,F"By voting against the Supplementary
OL,16,FBudget, Labour are not only voting
OL,17,Fagainst more money for children with
OL,18,Fadditional learning needs, money to
OL,19,Fcut waiting lists, and money to fund
OL,20,Fchildcare, they will also be teaming
OL,21,Fup with the Tories and Reform.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,432,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1784047674
OL,3,CWelsh Government set to lose
OL,4,Csupplementary Budget vote
OL,6,F"It is clear that they have learnt
OL,7,Fnothing from their humiliating
OL,8,Felection defeat in May. Wales rejected
OL,9,FLabour in May, but that doesn't mean
OL,10,FLabour should reject the priorities of
OL,11,Fthe people of Wales."
OL,13,FIn itself defeat tonight won't be
OL,14,Ffatal to the Welsh Government's
OL,15,Fsurvival - unlike a full budget, the
OL,16,FFinance Minister can simply table a
OL,17,Fnew supplementary budget.
OL,19,FBut it would be a blow and a reminder
OL,20,Fof how difficult minority government
OL,21,Fcan be.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/11
